Phishing and social engineering
How to prevent the attacks?
Two-factor, email spam filters, VPN,

Social Engineering: art of getting users to compromise information systems.

Phishing: An approach to capture users credentials. Include an URL in a mail etc...

Spear-Phshing: A mail tailor made to a user making it seem legit, with information gathered about the user.


Physical approaches: Actually gathering information in person. Eg dumpster searching...

Social approaches:

Reverse social engineering: Attacker sabotages a part of one's services, pretends to be a figure of assistance and ask for vital information to supposedly fix the problem.

Technical approaches: find information via the internet: LinkedIn, FaceBook, Instagram etc. web scraping

Socio-technical approaches: Combination of all approaches. eg baiting attack with road apples or spear-phishing.